<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you have fields in your database table with an empty string as a default value, Zend_Db_Table (_Row) will set / insert NULL instead of a string(0) "".</p>

<p>The bug is in Zend_Db_Table_Abstract: 1426 in the if clause:
($metadata['DEFAULT'] != null)</p>

<p>but it should be:
($metadata['DEFAULT'] !== null)</p>

    </div>
</div>

